<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="140" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1063,2030]" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">
—Another rare species in 
<collectingCountry box="[944,1085,1208,1232]" name="Serbia" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
. The only documented records have been published by Weiss (1975) and 
<bibRefCitation box="[634,974,1243,1268]" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" refId="ref11427" refString="Sobczyk, R. &amp; Gligorovic, B. (2016) Diversity of Butterflies in the Zeta-Skadar Plain, Montenegro. Acta Zoologica Bulgarica, 68 (2), 183 - 190." type="journal article">Sobczyk &amp; Gligorović (2016)</bibRefCitation>
from the area around Podgorica, and by 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,336,1279,1304]" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" refId="ref9759" refString="Kuhnert, H. (1971) Die Tagfalterbeobachtungen im Gebiet von Igalo (Montenegro). Entomologische Zeitschrift Frankfurt am Main, 81 (8), 73 - 93." type="journal article">Kühnert (1971)</bibRefCitation>
who reported it from the surroundings of Igalo. The species’ host plant (
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Astragalus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="monspessulanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">Astragalus monspessulanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.) has been recorded in the karst terrains around the capital (
<bibRefCitation box="[1033,1259,1315,1340]" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" refId="ref11462" refString="Stesevic, D., Cakovic, D. &amp; Jovanovic, S. (2014) The urban flora of Podgorica (Montenegro, SE Europe): annotated checklist, distribution atlas, habitats and life-forms, taxonomic, phytogeographical and ecological analysis. Ecologica Montenegrina, 1 (Supplementum), 1 - 171." type="journal article">
Stešević 
<emphasis box="[1135,1192,1315,1340]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hubner" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[1327,1436,1315,1340]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Polyommatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="escheri">
<emphasis box="[1327,1436,1315,1340]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">P. escheri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been reported from Gruda in 
<collectingCountry box="[523,608,1351,1376]" name="Croatia" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">Croatia</collectingCountry>
, very near the border with 
<collectingCountry box="[909,1046,1352,1376]" name="Serbia" pageId="12" pageNumber="140">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
(Williams pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
